  						<!--#beginContent#-->
  						<table align='center' cellpadding=5 width='85%'>  <tr><td class='spti2' width='100%'>PLAYER STRATEGY - CLERIC</td></tr>  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><font class='dbti'>GROUPING ALL THE WAY</font> - <small>Calliea Silvermyst, Tunare</td></tr>
  <tr><td width='100%' class='db'><p>For the clerics who think that undead soloing is possible,
think again. Unlike druids, clerics are not mana manachines.
True, our undead nukes do a great amount of damage and conserve a
lot of mana. But there aren't very many zones where you can solo
undead safely. The Lake of ill Omen is great, except there aren't
hundreds of skellies roaming everywhere. And there is a problem
with unrest. How are you going to get a skeletal monk out of the
house without pulling a barbed bone, too, and a festering hag,
and then training to the zone? And how can you find enough space
in the yard in unrest to do this without being trained every ten
seconds?<br>
Clerics are not soloing classes. If you wanted to solo, you'd be
a shaman or a druid. They can heal too, and buff, and shamans are
even better buffers (as far as adding to statistics). My advice
to you all is grouping. Unrest is the best place to be from
levels 14-17 in my humble opinion. After level 17, you're too
high for yard trash, and you'll only get trained and cause trains
if you try to take the first floor. Clearly, it's time to move
on. I suggest levels 18-22 go to the lake of ill omen to hunt.
(Although icy orcs in Everfrost isn't that bad, if you don't mind
the harmtouches.) The Sarnak Fortress is a great place to be,
great experience, not so great loot - but the real loot doesn't
start kicking in until level 30 anyway. I highly suggest starting
a group at the skeleton tower in the lake as well, levels 20-22.
Not only is the skeleton tower a good spot to pull from, the
experience is AMAZING. Undead is the best exp in the lake of ill
omen.. although the loot there isn't that great. At level 23, I'd
head back to unrest for one last hurrah. At this level you can
camp the bar and the magi room, great exp and some items that
people will actually buy. <br>
So you ding level 24, what are you going to do now? Hang around
in unrest (aka the sissy dungeon)? Here's some news for you,
clerics: you can now heal 300 HP at a time. It's time to move
onto bigger things. Cazic-Thule, Split-Paw, Frontier Mountains...
big bad mobs that hit for lots hanging out there. And druids and
shamans can't heal the tanks enough so you all clerics are on
high demand. I think Cazic Thule is probably the best 24-26. At
26 you'll get a bigger share of the exp killing giants in
Frontier Mountain, and, who knows, you might even get a Forest
Loop :). Also, it's time to start thinking about your cleric
quest armor, boys and gals. (Boots are probably the first thing
you'll want to get). <br>
One warning about Cazic-Thule: those lizards HATE HEALERS. Make
sure you go to CT with a tank that you know and love and trust
and can yell at and swear at when (s)he can't taunt the mobs off
you and you die. AND a note for split paw: hunt outside of it,
it's safer. Inside are these nasty little gnolls that get trained
to the zone a lot. If one of them charms you you'll start
whacking away at your group member :( Not pretty. Okay I'm done,
folks, but remember - just because you have pretty undead nukes
is NO excuse to nuke instead of heal. blah blah blah.<br>
</p>
</td></tr>
